<DOC><DOCNO> AP890314-0132 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-14-89 1445EST</FILEID><FIRST>d p AM-NYCMayor     03-14 0200</FIRST><SECOND>AM-NYC Mayor,0205</SECOND><HEAD>NYU Dean Announces for New York City Mayor</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Herb London, a syndicated columnist and dean ofan interdisciplinary studies department at New York University, onTuesday announced his candidacy for the Republican mayoralnomination.   London, a little-known conservative, faces Ronald Lauder, acosmetics fortune heir and former U.S. ambassador to Austria.Rudolph W. Giuliani, a former federal prosecutor, is expected toenter the race.   ``We will win by focusing on unique solutions to New York'schronic problems while Mr. Lauder campaigns against Mr. Giuliani's`liberalism' and Mr. Giuliani campaigns against Mr. Lauder'smoney,'' London said.   London said he favored privatization of city-run housing and theprompt auction of property taken by the city for back taxes. He alsofavors the death penalty for police- and drug-related killings.   London, 50, is dean of NYU's 1,000-student Gallatin Division,which he founded in 1972, and a senior fellow at the HudsonInstitute, a conservative think tank.   In the Democratic race, Mayor Edward I. Koch is expected to faceManhattan Borough President David Dinkins, Comptroller Harrison J.Goldin and real estate developer Richard Ravitch.   The primary is set for September and the general election forNovember.</TEXT></DOC>